WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.880 align:middle line:90%


00:00:10.880 --> 00:00:11.980 align:middle line:84%
Hello, my beautiful
co-creators.

00:00:11.980 --> 00:00:14.070 align:middle line:90%
Lilou, for Gaiam TV.

00:00:14.070 --> 00:00:18.080 align:middle line:84%
Today I'm in Orlando, Florida
with Michael Cooley, hello.

00:00:18.080 --> 00:00:18.950 align:middle line:90%
Hello, Lilou.

00:00:18.950 --> 00:00:19.720 align:middle line:90%
How are you doing?

00:00:19.720 --> 00:00:20.940 align:middle line:90%
I'm doing well, thank you.

00:00:20.940 --> 00:00:22.200 align:middle line:90%
It's beautiful out here.

00:00:22.200 --> 00:00:24.480 align:middle line:84%
Yes, definitely not
as cold as in Europe.

00:00:24.480 --> 00:00:26.890 align:middle line:84%
I had to come back to
the US a little bit.

00:00:26.890 --> 00:00:29.630 align:middle line:84%
Or as cold as in New
England, where I'm from.

00:00:29.630 --> 00:00:31.120 align:middle line:84%
It's really, really
cold up there, too.

00:00:31.120 --> 00:00:33.790 align:middle line:84%
So this is great-- great
place to get together.

00:00:33.790 --> 00:00:34.940 align:middle line:90%
Yes, and a great story.

00:00:34.940 --> 00:00:37.990 align:middle line:84%
You're going to be so
inspired by this story.

00:00:37.990 --> 00:00:39.740 align:middle line:84%
Tell us about your
background, because I

00:00:39.740 --> 00:00:41.120 align:middle line:90%
know you're an entrepreneur.

00:00:41.120 --> 00:00:42.710 align:middle line:90%
You're a CEO now and an author.

00:00:42.710 --> 00:00:46.340 align:middle line:84%
But this was definitely not
the case years and years ago,

00:00:46.340 --> 00:00:48.140 align:middle line:84%
when you went through
your rock bottom, which

00:00:48.140 --> 00:00:50.250 align:middle line:90%
is also the title of your book.

00:00:50.250 --> 00:00:52.670 align:middle line:84%
Tell us what you went through
so that we can understand.

00:00:52.670 --> 00:00:55.580 align:middle line:84%
And then we'll go into--
for everybody watching,

00:00:55.580 --> 00:00:59.860 align:middle line:84%
this is really about going
and reaching your dreams,

00:00:59.860 --> 00:01:01.470 align:middle line:90%
whatever your background.

00:01:01.470 --> 00:01:04.379 align:middle line:84%
you're definitely
the man that says

00:01:04.379 --> 00:01:06.490 align:middle line:84%
it's possible to live
those and to live

00:01:06.490 --> 00:01:08.010 align:middle line:90%
a successful, happy life.

00:01:08.010 --> 00:01:09.240 align:middle line:90%
Well, thank you.

00:01:09.240 --> 00:01:10.130 align:middle line:90%
Thank you for saying that.

00:01:10.130 --> 00:01:12.980 align:middle line:90%
And I so believe it myself.

00:01:12.980 --> 00:01:17.600 align:middle line:84%
The story of "Rock Bottom"
is the story of my background

00:01:17.600 --> 00:01:21.640 align:middle line:84%
as is child raised
between a broken home

00:01:21.640 --> 00:01:24.420 align:middle line:84%
with a mother who
was an alcoholic,

00:01:24.420 --> 00:01:27.330 align:middle line:84%
a father who was a
hard-working blue collar

00:01:27.330 --> 00:01:28.550 align:middle line:90%
worker, who remarried.

00:01:28.550 --> 00:01:31.800 align:middle line:84%
But he married into a family
where my stepmother, who

00:01:31.800 --> 00:01:35.690 align:middle line:84%
had two children of our own that
were older-- we quickly learned

00:01:35.690 --> 00:01:39.340 align:middle line:84%
going into that family
what child abuse was

00:01:39.340 --> 00:01:43.870 align:middle line:84%
from mental, physical, sexual,
emotional abuse that went on

00:01:43.870 --> 00:01:47.130 align:middle line:84%
in that family with my
little brother and me

00:01:47.130 --> 00:01:51.480 align:middle line:84%
for over a decade,
to my mother's home

00:01:51.480 --> 00:01:52.850 align:middle line:84%
up in Saint Louis,
where we moved

00:01:52.850 --> 00:01:56.030 align:middle line:84%
from apartment to apartment
to apartment, kicked out.

00:01:56.030 --> 00:01:57.360 align:middle line:90%
She was an alcoholic.

00:01:57.360 --> 00:02:01.950 align:middle line:84%
We had nine different
step fathers growing up.

00:02:01.950 --> 00:02:03.080 align:middle line:90%
There was abuse there.

00:02:03.080 --> 00:02:05.870 align:middle line:84%
So we went from one
abusive home to another,

00:02:05.870 --> 00:02:07.710 align:middle line:84%
never went to the
same elementary school

00:02:07.710 --> 00:02:11.400 align:middle line:84%
twice in a row in a year, and
sometimes went to and three

00:02:11.400 --> 00:02:12.410 align:middle line:90%
different elementary schools.

00:02:12.410 --> 00:02:16.070 align:middle line:84%
So we were traveling all
over, going through this abuse

00:02:16.070 --> 00:02:20.890 align:middle line:84%
until I reached the point at
15 where I left home for good.

00:02:20.890 --> 00:02:22.230 align:middle line:90%
I went out on the road.

00:02:22.230 --> 00:02:23.310 align:middle line:90%
I hitchhiked all over.

00:02:23.310 --> 00:02:25.890 align:middle line:90%
I lived on the streets.

00:02:25.890 --> 00:02:31.840 align:middle line:84%
I ended up in St. Louis sleeping
in alleyways and rooftops

00:02:31.840 --> 00:02:36.150 align:middle line:84%
and any shanty I could
find, beg, borrowing,

00:02:36.150 --> 00:02:37.530 align:middle line:90%
and stealing for money.

00:02:37.530 --> 00:02:39.190 align:middle line:90%
Ended up finding a new family.

00:02:39.190 --> 00:02:41.872 align:middle line:84%
That family turned out
to be a street gang.

00:02:41.872 --> 00:02:42.905 align:middle line:90%
We ended up running the street.

00:02:42.905 --> 00:02:46.250 align:middle line:84%
It was a lot of kids that
were lost, like I was,

00:02:46.250 --> 00:02:49.130 align:middle line:84%
going to abusive situations
with their families.

00:02:49.130 --> 00:02:54.580 align:middle line:84%
In the end, we were a group of
kids that were filled with rage

00:02:54.580 --> 00:02:56.360 align:middle line:84%
and anger, and we
were out hurting

00:02:56.360 --> 00:03:00.290 align:middle line:84%
people and doing bad things
and getting in trouble.

00:03:00.290 --> 00:03:05.230 align:middle line:84%
It landed me in lockup
and incarceration.

00:03:05.230 --> 00:03:08.100 align:middle line:84%
Then eventually--
I'm now my 20s--

00:03:08.100 --> 00:03:10.920 align:middle line:90%
Not now, but you were then.

00:03:10.920 --> 00:03:14.250 align:middle line:84%
No, now, as the
story goes, right?

00:03:14.250 --> 00:03:16.690 align:middle line:90%
Even though I may look 20--no.

00:03:16.690 --> 00:03:21.660 align:middle line:84%
Definitely not 20-- but in my
20 I was hitting rock bottom,

00:03:21.660 --> 00:03:25.630 align:middle line:84%
living out of a broken down car,
getting cleaned up in a rest

00:03:25.630 --> 00:03:30.210 align:middle line:84%
stop, traveling aimlessly
with nowhere to go,

00:03:30.210 --> 00:03:33.200 align:middle line:84%
trying to get gas
money, in lockup again.

00:03:33.200 --> 00:03:35.890 align:middle line:84%
And I actually hit
rock bottom, and that

00:03:35.890 --> 00:03:38.320 align:middle line:90%
was the end of the road for me.

00:03:38.320 --> 00:03:41.010 align:middle line:84%
And if I was going to
stay on this path I was

00:03:41.010 --> 00:03:45.030 align:middle line:84%
going to stay on, I was going
to end up dead, in prison,

00:03:45.030 --> 00:03:46.720 align:middle line:90%
or insane.

00:03:46.720 --> 00:03:50.860 align:middle line:84%
So I took a road that I'd
never been down before.

00:03:50.860 --> 00:03:53.750 align:middle line:84%
I took a job in a mail
room at minimum wage.

00:03:53.750 --> 00:03:56.720 align:middle line:84%
I met some incredible people
who helped me along the way, who

00:03:56.720 --> 00:03:59.820 align:middle line:84%
inspired me, who
helped me learn,

00:03:59.820 --> 00:04:03.740 align:middle line:84%
help me to get an education,
helped me to get a good job.

00:04:03.740 --> 00:04:07.380 align:middle line:84%
And they taught me
how to be human again.

00:04:07.380 --> 00:04:09.231 align:middle line:84%
Because you felt
like an animal before.

00:04:09.231 --> 00:04:09.930 align:middle line:90%
I did.

00:04:09.930 --> 00:04:11.760 align:middle line:84%
I felt like an animal
that was caged.

00:04:11.760 --> 00:04:13.275 align:middle line:84%
And what happens
when an animal who

00:04:13.275 --> 00:04:16.420 align:middle line:84%
is caged, who was
constantly beaten, as I felt

00:04:16.420 --> 00:04:19.860 align:middle line:84%
happened as I was
a kid and teenager?

00:04:19.860 --> 00:04:21.420 align:middle line:90%
They do one of two things.

00:04:21.420 --> 00:04:26.660 align:middle line:84%
Either they curl up and die, or
they lash out in rage as soon

00:04:26.660 --> 00:04:27.680 align:middle line:90%
as they have the chance.

00:04:27.680 --> 00:04:29.580 align:middle line:90%
Well, I did the latter.

00:04:29.580 --> 00:04:31.720 align:middle line:84%
I lashed out in rage,
ran the streets,

00:04:31.720 --> 00:04:33.900 align:middle line:90%
and it was a crazy time.

00:04:33.900 --> 00:04:36.740 align:middle line:84%
And I was destined
to die, but I chose

00:04:36.740 --> 00:04:38.330 align:middle line:84%
this path that I'd
never been down

00:04:38.330 --> 00:04:40.640 align:middle line:90%
before, where I knew no one.

00:04:40.640 --> 00:04:45.100 align:middle line:84%
Before I chose this path, nobody
wanted anything to do with me.

00:04:45.100 --> 00:04:46.350 align:middle line:90%
I was that animal.

00:04:46.350 --> 00:04:48.170 align:middle line:90%
I was dangerous.

00:04:48.170 --> 00:04:49.740 align:middle line:90%
People were afraid of me.

00:04:49.740 --> 00:04:52.770 align:middle line:84%
And when I took that path
that I took down that road

00:04:52.770 --> 00:04:57.090 align:middle line:84%
and I met the people that I met,
I joined the company I joined.

00:04:57.090 --> 00:05:00.180 align:middle line:84%
I then developed out
to be human again,

00:05:00.180 --> 00:05:03.670 align:middle line:84%
learned how to be
socially aware,

00:05:03.670 --> 00:05:07.550 align:middle line:84%
and actually learned
how to communicate.

00:05:07.550 --> 00:05:09.410 align:middle line:84%
Some people say I still
can't communicate,

00:05:09.410 --> 00:05:13.390 align:middle line:84%
but I talk better than used
to, let me tell you that.

00:05:13.390 --> 00:05:15.150 align:middle line:90%
And so I went down this road.

00:05:15.150 --> 00:05:16.930 align:middle line:90%
I developed my career.

00:05:16.930 --> 00:05:19.070 align:middle line:84%
I went from the mail
room at minimum wage

00:05:19.070 --> 00:05:21.950 align:middle line:84%
to senior vice president of
operations for a $40 million

00:05:21.950 --> 00:05:23.300 align:middle line:90%
consulting firm.

00:05:23.300 --> 00:05:25.200 align:middle line:84%
I went on there
to senior director

00:05:25.200 --> 00:05:28.160 align:middle line:84%
of administration
for a $70 million

00:05:28.160 --> 00:05:30.800 align:middle line:90%
health care records company.

00:05:30.800 --> 00:05:33.170 align:middle line:84%
And then from there I was
recruited out of Dallas

00:05:33.170 --> 00:05:36.180 align:middle line:84%
up to New England, where
for the last six years

00:05:36.180 --> 00:05:42.430 align:middle line:84%
have been the CEO of a national
records management company.

00:05:42.430 --> 00:05:45.890 align:middle line:90%
And so I have a great family.

00:05:45.890 --> 00:05:48.010 align:middle line:90%
I have a great wife and kids.

00:05:48.010 --> 00:05:50.910 align:middle line:84%
I have a great company
I work for, great people

00:05:50.910 --> 00:05:52.720 align:middle line:90%
that I'm surrounded by.

00:05:52.720 --> 00:05:56.990 align:middle line:84%
All of that said, I just
shouldn't be this lucky.

00:05:56.990 --> 00:05:58.450 align:middle line:84%
So after going
through everything

00:05:58.450 --> 00:06:00.080 align:middle line:84%
I went through, having
everything I have

00:06:00.080 --> 00:06:02.050 align:middle line:90%
today, I look in the mirror.

00:06:02.050 --> 00:06:02.910 align:middle line:90%
I think about it.

00:06:02.910 --> 00:06:05.470 align:middle line:84%
I say, you know,
this story needs

00:06:05.470 --> 00:06:07.200 align:middle line:90%
to be an example for others.

00:06:07.200 --> 00:06:11.320 align:middle line:84%
So maybe I can use my past to
help others with their future.

00:06:11.320 --> 00:06:15.090 align:middle line:84%
I know you speak in
companies and in prisons

00:06:15.090 --> 00:06:18.390 align:middle line:84%
also in home shelters
and everywhere,

00:06:18.390 --> 00:06:21.820 align:middle line:84%
and your true heart desire
is to inspire people.

00:06:21.820 --> 00:06:26.980 align:middle line:84%
Here, I feel for people
looking for their purpose

00:06:26.980 --> 00:06:29.230 align:middle line:84%
or something, or at
least a meaning in life,

00:06:29.230 --> 00:06:31.210 align:middle line:84%
because, I guess, did
you have a meaning?

00:06:31.210 --> 00:06:36.480 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you were just
surviving at that time, right?

00:06:36.480 --> 00:06:38.630 align:middle line:84%
That's all it
was, was a survival

00:06:38.630 --> 00:06:41.350 align:middle line:90%
instinct, just to survive.

00:06:41.350 --> 00:06:45.640 align:middle line:84%
But the whole-- so you'd think
that the end of the story,

00:06:45.640 --> 00:06:48.360 align:middle line:84%
the end of "Rock Bottom"
from the streets to success

00:06:48.360 --> 00:06:50.560 align:middle line:84%
could be I went
from the streets,

00:06:50.560 --> 00:06:53.490 align:middle line:84%
and now I have what
many deem to be success.

00:06:53.490 --> 00:06:54.664 align:middle line:90%
You head up a company.

00:06:54.664 --> 00:06:56.020 align:middle line:84%
You've got a great family.
You've got the house.

00:06:56.020 --> 00:06:56.719 align:middle line:90%
You've got the car.

00:06:56.719 --> 00:06:59.870 align:middle line:84%
You've got the
community involvement.

00:06:59.870 --> 00:07:00.810 align:middle line:90%
You've got all that.

00:07:00.810 --> 00:07:04.230 align:middle line:84%
But at the end of the
day, my real success

00:07:04.230 --> 00:07:10.830 align:middle line:84%
comes from what I'm able to do
today, which is to your comment

00:07:10.830 --> 00:07:12.110 align:middle line:90%
I speak to groups.

00:07:12.110 --> 00:07:13.320 align:middle line:90%
I speak to people.

00:07:13.320 --> 00:07:16.560 align:middle line:84%
And what I try to do is try
to use my story to maybe help

00:07:16.560 --> 00:07:19.670 align:middle line:84%
not only those who are trying
to come from rock bottom,

00:07:19.670 --> 00:07:23.300 align:middle line:84%
but those who already have
success, they have all of that.

00:07:23.300 --> 00:07:25.430 align:middle line:84%
But they still have a
real purpose in life.

00:07:25.430 --> 00:07:27.890 align:middle line:84%
It's all about making money,
the bottom line, what trip we're

00:07:27.890 --> 00:07:29.500 align:middle line:90%
going on, how big our house is.

00:07:29.500 --> 00:07:32.740 align:middle line:84%
And what I've learned that
it's much more than that.

00:07:32.740 --> 00:07:37.050 align:middle line:84%
To me, when I look at my kids,
and I try to develop character

00:07:37.050 --> 00:07:40.460 align:middle line:84%
in them, and I have them come
with me when I'm speaking

00:07:40.460 --> 00:07:44.520 align:middle line:84%
at homeless shelters or
prisons and how can we

00:07:44.520 --> 00:07:48.810 align:middle line:84%
help as a society to
inspire people to,

00:07:48.810 --> 00:07:50.670 align:middle line:84%
no matter what their
circumstances are,

00:07:50.670 --> 00:07:53.900 align:middle line:84%
to change it and be more
than they ever thought

00:07:53.900 --> 00:07:55.980 align:middle line:84%
could happen based on
how they were raised.

00:07:55.980 --> 00:08:01.660 align:middle line:84%
I was the kid that was told
that you'll never be anything,

00:08:01.660 --> 00:08:04.540 align:middle line:84%
I wish you were never
born, I wish you were dead,

00:08:04.540 --> 00:08:09.580 align:middle line:84%
I want you out, and not just by
parents, but by other people,

00:08:09.580 --> 00:08:11.380 align:middle line:90%
by stepfamily.

00:08:11.380 --> 00:08:13.190 align:middle line:84%
They just didn't want
anything to do with me.

00:08:13.190 --> 00:08:16.140 align:middle line:84%
We were the kids that never
should have been born.

00:08:16.140 --> 00:08:20.140 align:middle line:84%
But yet today we are
able to give back.

00:08:20.140 --> 00:08:22.480 align:middle line:84%
My little brother who went
through the same situation

00:08:22.480 --> 00:08:26.060 align:middle line:84%
as I have, he has three
successful car dealerships

00:08:26.060 --> 00:08:29.230 align:middle line:84%
in St. Louis, and he
has incredible family,

00:08:29.230 --> 00:08:32.380 align:middle line:84%
and his children
are doing very well.

00:08:32.380 --> 00:08:36.860 align:middle line:84%
Collectively, we are
hopefully examples of people;

00:08:36.860 --> 00:08:39.480 align:middle line:84%
no matter how low
your rock bottom is,

00:08:39.480 --> 00:08:40.830 align:middle line:84%
you can be anything
you want to be.

00:08:40.830 --> 00:08:43.250 align:middle line:84%
But once you get
there, once you get

00:08:43.250 --> 00:08:47.360 align:middle line:84%
to becoming human again, what
are you going to do with that?

00:08:47.360 --> 00:08:50.340 align:middle line:84%
But I guess not everybody
went through such

00:08:50.340 --> 00:08:53.590 align:middle line:84%
a huge rock bottom,
but we maybe went

00:08:53.590 --> 00:08:56.800 align:middle line:84%
through different versions of
that and different messages

00:08:56.800 --> 00:08:58.780 align:middle line:90%
that we received growing up.

00:08:58.780 --> 00:09:02.380 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes when we don't hit
that rock bottom, where we're

00:09:02.380 --> 00:09:07.910 align:middle line:84%
in a situation where we can
be very a sad or even angry

00:09:07.910 --> 00:09:11.110 align:middle line:84%
or don't know how to get
out of the situation,

00:09:11.110 --> 00:09:15.710 align:middle line:84%
what is your
recommendation to step out

00:09:15.710 --> 00:09:19.710 align:middle line:84%
and to live kind of
like you're lucky now.

00:09:19.710 --> 00:09:21.620 align:middle line:84%
You live it, and
your brother, too.

00:09:21.620 --> 00:09:24.190 align:middle line:84%
Is that something
that was on your past?

00:09:24.190 --> 00:09:27.430 align:middle line:84%
Was that really a commitment
of yours at some point?

00:09:27.430 --> 00:09:30.100 align:middle line:84%
Well, you know, I believe in
fate, and there's a lot of fate

00:09:30.100 --> 00:09:34.580 align:middle line:84%
involved with my life and
what's happened in that regard.

00:09:34.580 --> 00:09:37.080 align:middle line:84%
However, from a
purpose standpoint,

00:09:37.080 --> 00:09:41.760 align:middle line:84%
I had to learn how to do
everything again, including

00:09:41.760 --> 00:09:43.770 align:middle line:84%
just being out here
in front of people,

00:09:43.770 --> 00:09:45.720 align:middle line:84%
to be speaking in
front of people.

00:09:45.720 --> 00:09:49.060 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I was the guy that
if we had a big meeting,

00:09:49.060 --> 00:09:50.800 align:middle line:84%
would hide behind a
curtain because he didn't

00:09:50.800 --> 00:09:52.650 align:middle line:84%
want to be called on
or noticed because

00:09:52.650 --> 00:09:54.810 align:middle line:90%
of my incredible insecurity.

00:09:54.810 --> 00:09:57.670 align:middle line:84%
But now today I'm speaking
to thousands of people,

00:09:57.670 --> 00:09:59.310 align:middle line:84%
and they can't
get me to shut up.

00:09:59.310 --> 00:10:03.710 align:middle line:84%
But it's more then just being
out there speaking to people,

00:10:03.710 --> 00:10:05.490 align:middle line:84%
telling the story
of "Rock Bottom."

00:10:05.490 --> 00:10:08.060 align:middle line:84%
It's more about how
you can connect the two

00:10:08.060 --> 00:10:11.620 align:middle line:84%
haves with the have nots and
how you can make a difference

00:10:11.620 --> 00:10:14.420 align:middle line:90%
on a larger more global scale.

00:10:14.420 --> 00:10:18.420 align:middle line:84%
For example, I'll be speaking
in a homeless shelter at night.

00:10:18.420 --> 00:10:20.750 align:middle line:84%
And the next day
as a CEO, I might

00:10:20.750 --> 00:10:26.780 align:middle line:84%
be signing a six-figure
