Everybody's using me.

00:11:52.420 --> 00:11:56.440 align:middle line:84%
Well, to that end, to this
day, I tell everybody I talk

00:11:56.440 --> 00:11:58.940 align:middle line:90%
to that I want you to use me.

00:11:58.940 --> 00:12:01.970 align:middle line:84%
How can you use
me to help others?

00:12:01.970 --> 00:12:04.070 align:middle line:90%
And how can you use this story?

00:12:04.070 --> 00:12:10.640 align:middle line:84%
And that is my passion is to
see what happens to people when

00:12:10.640 --> 00:12:12.510 align:middle line:84%
college kids and speak
at the university

00:12:12.510 --> 00:12:14.820 align:middle line:84%
are getting ready to
start their whole career

00:12:14.820 --> 00:12:17.390 align:middle line:84%
and their whole
life, and they're

00:12:17.390 --> 00:12:19.740 align:middle line:84%
trying to decide what they're
going to do with their future,

00:12:19.740 --> 00:12:22.780 align:middle line:84%
and they hear a story like
this, whatever they're doing

00:12:22.780 --> 00:12:25.550 align:middle line:84%
in their future, they
can tie the inspiration

00:12:25.550 --> 00:12:28.050 align:middle line:84%
that they can become to
help others along the way.

00:12:28.050 --> 00:12:30.270 align:middle line:84%
And that's the kind of
stuff that's really truly

00:12:30.270 --> 00:12:34.560 align:middle line:84%
moving to me and gives
me great gratitude,

00:12:34.560 --> 00:12:39.520 align:middle line:84%
gives me great appreciation
for what I've gone through.

00:12:39.520 --> 00:12:40.970 align:middle line:84%
So that's what you
recommend to kids,

00:12:40.970 --> 00:12:42.550 align:middle line:84%
let's say, to kids
coming out of school?

00:12:42.550 --> 00:12:43.840 align:middle line:90%
What would you tell them?

00:12:43.840 --> 00:12:47.180 align:middle line:84%
Do really just serve
unconditionally and let

00:12:47.180 --> 00:12:50.610 align:middle line:84%
life bring you, or also,
are you into planning,

00:12:50.610 --> 00:12:53.760 align:middle line:84%
or what is your recommendation
to them for their future,

00:12:53.760 --> 00:12:57.010 align:middle line:84%
and which we can all apply
anywhere we're at in our Life

00:12:57.010 --> 00:13:00.830 align:middle line:84%
Absolutely, and actually, it's
going to be each person's going

00:13:00.830 --> 00:13:02.380 align:middle line:90%
to develop their own path.

00:13:02.380 --> 00:13:05.190 align:middle line:84%
But the two things you
said were critical.

00:13:05.190 --> 00:13:08.560 align:middle line:84%
One is everything is
done with a purpose.

00:13:08.560 --> 00:13:11.450 align:middle line:90%
There's a plan.

00:13:11.450 --> 00:13:14.170 align:middle line:84%
I'm a very detailed planner
from the moment I get up,

00:13:14.170 --> 00:13:15.640 align:middle line:90%
to the end the day.

00:13:15.640 --> 00:13:18.220 align:middle line:84%
And so there's
planning about it,

00:13:18.220 --> 00:13:25.120 align:middle line:84%
but there's also the opportunity
of unconditional assistance

00:13:25.120 --> 00:13:26.510 align:middle line:90%
whenever it's needed.

00:13:26.510 --> 00:13:28.750 align:middle line:84%
So you might have a plan
throughout your day,

00:13:28.750 --> 00:13:31.960 align:middle line:84%
and then you'll get a call
that somebody needs some help,

00:13:31.960 --> 00:13:36.070 align:middle line:84%
and you need to stop what you're
doing because that person,

00:13:36.070 --> 00:13:37.790 align:middle line:84%
you might be the helping
hand that changes

00:13:37.790 --> 00:13:39.310 align:middle line:90%
their life in that regard.

00:13:39.310 --> 00:13:42.170 align:middle line:84%
And so now that I do this
speaking, I get a lot of those

00:13:42.170 --> 00:13:47.050 align:middle line:84%
calls from somebody with a
challenge with their daughter

00:13:47.050 --> 00:13:50.360 align:middle line:84%
or their son, or somebody
incarcerated will write me

00:13:50.360 --> 00:13:52.260 align:middle line:84%
from prison with
their challenges,

00:13:52.260 --> 00:13:54.820 align:middle line:84%
and if I can help somebody who
will be getting out of prison

00:13:54.820 --> 00:13:56.740 align:middle line:90%
and be in a halfway house.

00:13:56.740 --> 00:13:59.820 align:middle line:84%
A business leader who has
everything in the world, that

00:13:59.820 --> 00:14:03.250 align:middle line:84%
running a large
company, but they're

00:14:03.250 --> 00:14:06.060 align:middle line:84%
challenged with their
daughter, what can

00:14:06.060 --> 00:14:08.940 align:middle line:84%
I do to give back
in that regard?

00:14:08.940 --> 00:14:11.140 align:middle line:84%
And they want to know
how they can help.

00:14:11.140 --> 00:14:14.460 align:middle line:84%
To the Catholic
Diocese or a church

00:14:14.460 --> 00:14:20.030 align:middle line:84%
that may contact you to say,
how can we reach these teens?

00:14:20.030 --> 00:14:22.500 align:middle line:84%
Those are the things
that I look for.

00:14:22.500 --> 00:14:25.600 align:middle line:84%
So you have your plan, and you
look for these fateful things

00:14:25.600 --> 00:14:27.400 align:middle line:84%
that come your way,
and you say that you're

00:14:27.400 --> 00:14:30.600 align:middle line:84%
just called to go do something
unconditionally in that regard.

00:14:30.600 --> 00:14:33.640 align:middle line:84%
So yeah, I agree that you
have to be prepared for that.

00:14:33.640 --> 00:14:36.410 align:middle line:84%
You have to be prepared for
the life you want to live.

00:14:36.410 --> 00:14:40.950 align:middle line:84%
If it's in college,
getting an education,

00:14:40.950 --> 00:14:43.200 align:middle line:84%
building your future,
getting a good job.

00:14:43.200 --> 00:14:44.740 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, that may be
your plan to do

00:14:44.740 --> 00:14:47.880 align:middle line:84%
that, but never
forget the that's just

00:14:47.880 --> 00:14:50.330 align:middle line:90%
a means to get you through.

00:14:50.330 --> 00:14:52.250 align:middle line:84%
But life is a
long, long journey,

00:14:52.250 --> 00:14:54.400 align:middle line:84%
so you're going to find a point
where you're going to need

00:14:54.400 --> 00:14:59.410 align:middle line:84%
a purpose, and it goes way
beyond how big your house

00:14:59.410 --> 00:15:00.840 align:middle line:90%
is, how much money you have.

00:15:00.840 --> 00:15:01.870 align:middle line:90%
It goes beyond.

00:15:01.870 --> 00:15:05.320 align:middle line:84%
You have to do something for
your soul and for hopefully

00:15:05.320 --> 00:15:08.860 align:middle line:84%
to help the souls of others,
and that's what I hope to leave,

00:15:08.860 --> 00:15:10.710 align:middle line:90%
when I leave as a legacy.

00:15:10.710 --> 00:15:14.160 align:middle line:84%
I hope my kids carry it on
[INAUDIBLE] to helping others.

00:15:14.160 --> 00:15:16.690 align:middle line:90%


00:15:16.690 --> 00:15:20.320 align:middle line:84%
And that's a lot to say
for somebody who was angry

00:15:20.320 --> 00:15:22.950 align:middle line:84%
at the world and felt
wronged by the world,

00:15:22.950 --> 00:15:24.760 align:middle line:90%
and felt abused to say--

00:15:24.760 --> 00:15:25.920 align:middle line:90%
Not worthy,

00:15:25.920 --> 00:15:27.980 align:middle line:84%
--and not worthy at
all, and felt like he

00:15:27.980 --> 00:15:29.940 align:middle line:90%
didn't deserve to be alive.

00:15:29.940 --> 00:15:33.650 align:middle line:84%
And then now today I'm
saying, I'm not doing enough.

00:15:33.650 --> 00:15:34.520 align:middle line:90%
I've got to do more.

00:15:34.520 --> 00:15:35.810 align:middle line:90%
I've got to get out there.

00:15:35.810 --> 00:15:38.860 align:middle line:84%
I've got to get more
in front of people.

00:15:38.860 --> 00:15:42.270 align:middle line:84%
And so what I tried to do was
stories like this was speaking

00:15:42.270 --> 00:15:46.870 align:middle line:84%
my story to get an audience to
say, maybe of the 200 people

00:15:46.870 --> 00:15:48.820 align:middle line:84%
you speak to, maybe a
couple of them are moved,

00:15:48.820 --> 00:15:50.790 align:middle line:84%
and they go out and
change the world.

00:15:50.790 --> 00:15:54.150 align:middle line:84%
And the incredible people I've
met along the way, that's kind

00:15:54.150 --> 00:15:55.730 align:middle line:90%
of been their purpose as well.

00:15:55.730 --> 00:15:58.480 align:middle line:84%
And it's just been really
moving for me and inspirational,

00:15:58.480 --> 00:16:02.360 align:middle line:84%
and it kind of drives me
in who I am today, I think.

00:16:02.360 --> 00:16:04.070 align:middle line:84%
And in those hard
moments, I guess,

00:16:04.070 --> 00:16:09.540 align:middle line:84%
you still have them, moments,
what do you go back to?

00:16:09.540 --> 00:16:11.850 align:middle line:84%
And I do drawback, but
here's the main point.

00:16:11.850 --> 00:16:15.100 align:middle line:84%
[INAUDIBLE] I can help out in
this way-- basketball game,

00:16:15.100 --> 00:16:16.660 align:middle line:84%
and your daughter's
cheerleading,

00:16:16.660 --> 00:16:20.110 align:middle line:84%
and you have to
divide and conquer.

00:16:20.110 --> 00:16:26.430 align:middle line:84%
But my most hectic day
today, or my worst day today,

00:16:26.430 --> 00:16:30.520 align:middle line:84%
is better than my
best day 25 years ago.

00:16:30.520 --> 00:16:33.640 align:middle line:84%
And so believe me, I
like those challenges.

00:16:33.640 --> 00:16:36.620 align:middle line:84%
But you do have to manage
and plan it and decide

00:16:36.620 --> 00:16:38.974 align:middle line:90%
you can only deliver so much.

00:16:38.974 --> 00:16:44.750 align:middle line:84%
Do you live a life of--
and please come back here.

00:16:44.750 --> 00:16:48.690 align:middle line:84%
Is it about being 100%
responsible in our lives

00:16:48.690 --> 00:16:49.540 align:middle line:90%
for what happens?

00:16:49.540 --> 00:16:51.050 align:middle line:90%
How do you see that?

00:16:51.050 --> 00:16:53.070 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, and that is the truth.

00:16:53.070 --> 00:16:55.720 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you have
to make that choice

00:16:55.720 --> 00:16:59.910 align:middle line:84%
in your life to be responsible
and take responsibility for it.

00:16:59.910 --> 00:17:02.740 align:middle line:84%
And the blame game is only
going to get your so far.

00:17:02.740 --> 00:17:04.760 align:middle line:84%
And at the end, it's
still going to come

00:17:04.760 --> 00:17:06.170 align:middle line:90%
back to what you can do.

00:17:06.170 --> 00:17:09.950 align:middle line:84%
Again, when you want
to know how that works,

00:17:09.950 --> 00:17:14.250 align:middle line:84%
have a day when nobody's
there, and you have

00:17:14.250 --> 00:17:16.329 align:middle line:90%
nobody there to assist you.

00:17:16.329 --> 00:17:19.220 align:middle line:84%
And you have to make
those decisions.

00:17:19.220 --> 00:17:22.220 align:middle line:84%
That's the kind of choices
you should make about life.

00:17:22.220 --> 00:17:25.300 align:middle line:84%
And whether it's your boss
breathing down your neck,

00:17:25.300 --> 00:17:30.220 align:middle line:84%
whether it's your [INAUDIBLE]
want you to do something,

00:17:30.220 --> 00:17:33.890 align:middle line:84%
you have so many things
going on, at the end the day,

00:17:33.890 --> 00:17:35.930 align:middle line:84%
you're going to have
to take responsibility

00:17:35.930 --> 00:17:37.540 align:middle line:90%
for those choices that you make.

00:17:37.540 --> 00:17:39.570 align:middle line:84%
You may not control how
people respond to you,

00:17:39.570 --> 00:17:41.190 align:middle line:84%
but you have to
be able to control

00:17:41.190 --> 00:17:45.720 align:middle line:84%
how you respond to people
in challenges and so on.

00:17:45.720 --> 00:17:47.030 align:middle line:90%
So that's what you can control.

00:17:47.030 --> 00:17:49.210 align:middle line:84%
So at the end the day, it
is only up to you, isn't it?

00:17:49.210 --> 00:17:50.810 align:middle line:90%
It is not to somebody else.

00:17:50.810 --> 00:17:52.940 align:middle line:84%
At least, that's the way
I choose to feel about it.

00:17:52.940 --> 00:17:55.750 align:middle line:84%
And when you have
kids that have-- it's

00:17:55.750 --> 00:17:58.540 align:middle line:84%
a problem in the US--
that have problems

00:17:58.540 --> 00:18:02.050 align:middle line:84%
with drugs or even
alcohol at a young age,

00:18:02.050 --> 00:18:04.090 align:middle line:90%
what's your advice on that?

00:18:04.090 --> 00:18:06.210 align:middle line:84%
Like kids that refuse
authority, that

00:18:06.210 --> 00:18:11.250 align:middle line:84%
want to just really the
break the whole-- no family,

00:18:11.250 --> 00:18:15.650 align:middle line:84%
I mean, for whatever
reason the parents

00:18:15.650 --> 00:18:18.650 align:middle line:84%
are in this situation of having
kids with an addiction problem,

00:18:18.650 --> 00:18:19.610 align:middle line:90%
what do you say?

00:18:19.610 --> 00:18:25.470 align:middle line:84%
Right, and again,
you're exactly right.

00:18:25.470 --> 00:18:28.120 align:middle line:84%
When it has to do
with drugs, it's

00:18:28.120 --> 00:18:30.690 align:middle line:84%
the worst case
scenario for a parent.

00:18:30.690 --> 00:18:32.670 align:middle line:84%
[INAUDIBLE] that just because
they went through abuse,

00:18:32.670 --> 00:18:34.730 align:middle line:84%
that was an excuse
for me to do drugs.

00:18:34.730 --> 00:18:36.650 align:middle line:90%
Again, that was not.

00:18:36.650 --> 00:18:39.190 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of kids out
there experiment who

00:18:39.190 --> 00:18:42.010 align:middle line:84%
have great parents, and they're
doing the best they can,

00:18:42.010 --> 00:18:43.690 align:middle line:84%
and then they get
hit with something

00:18:43.690 --> 00:18:45.870 align:middle line:90%
devastating like that.

00:18:45.870 --> 00:18:47.520 align:middle line:84%
They don't know how
to respond, especially

00:18:47.520 --> 00:18:50.150 align:middle line:84%
those who've never
done drugs themselves,

00:18:50.150 --> 00:18:51.770 align:middle line:90%
and their children are doing it.

00:18:51.770 --> 00:18:55.290 align:middle line:84%
It is a scary, scary
thing that you would find

00:18:55.290 --> 00:18:56.640 align:middle line:90%
yourself laying awake at night.

00:18:56.640 --> 00:18:59.740 align:middle line:84%
And this is what I hear from
the people that I'm speaking to.

00:18:59.740 --> 00:19:01.870 align:middle line:84%
And I'm trying to
help where I can,

00:19:01.870 --> 00:19:03.600 align:middle line:90%
using my background experience.

00:19:03.600 --> 00:19:07.710 align:middle line:84%
But I think the key
is from day one,

00:19:07.710 --> 00:19:10.400 align:middle line:84%
you have to be involved
with your kids' lives--

00:19:10.400 --> 00:19:13.130 align:middle line:90%
from day one.

00:19:13.130 --> 00:19:15.320 align:middle line:84%
And you have to
be a partnership.

00:19:15.320 --> 00:19:19.130 align:middle line:84%
If you're a single parent,
it is challenging enough,

00:19:19.130 --> 00:19:21.140 align:middle line:84%
but if you're a
husband and wife,

00:19:21.140 --> 00:19:23.090 align:middle line:84%
you have to be in
connection, and you

00:19:23.090 --> 00:19:24.680 align:middle line:84%
have to be a part
of your kid's life,

00:19:24.680 --> 00:19:27.070 align:middle line:84%
and you have to
divide and conquer.

00:19:27.070 --> 00:19:30.460 align:middle line:84%
Like we have two kids, and
the thing I say right now

00:19:30.460 --> 00:19:32.910 align:middle line:84%
is at least it's two
against two, right?

00:19:32.910 --> 00:19:35.610 align:middle line:84%
But when you have parents
that are on their own,

00:19:35.610 --> 00:19:38.230 align:middle line:84%
they have to stay involved
in their kid's life,

00:19:38.230 --> 00:19:40.202 align:middle line:84%
and they have to stay
involved throughout,

00:19:40.202 --> 00:19:41.235 align:middle line:90%
and they have to ask questions.

00:19:41.235 --> 00:19:42.700 align:middle line:90%
They have to be involved.

00:19:42.700 --> 00:19:44.390 align:middle line:90%
They can't be their best friend.

00:19:44.390 --> 00:19:47.460 align:middle line:84%
They've got to be
parents from the end

00:19:47.460 --> 00:19:50.860 align:middle line:84%
because those kids need them
to guide them through that part

00:19:50.860 --> 00:19:51.560 align:middle line:90%
of their life.

00:19:51.560 --> 00:19:54.275 align:middle line:84%
But let's say you find out that
your kid is in that situation,

00:19:54.275 --> 00:20:00.110 align:middle line:84%
and one of them is having a big
drug issue, how would you react

00:20:00.110 --> 00:20:02.420 align:middle line:84%
or how would you take
it from that point?

00:20:02.420 --> 00:20:03.650 align:middle line:90%
It starts there.

00:20:03.650 --> 00:20:05.345 align:middle line:84%
It starts with when
you discover that

00:20:05.345 --> 00:20:07.040 align:middle line:84%
and when you find
that out, and then

00:20:07.040 --> 00:20:10.210 align:middle line:84%
the talking that goes on behind
it, sitting down with them,

00:20:10.210 --> 00:20:11.780 align:middle line:90%
talking with them about it.

00:20:11.780 --> 00:20:13.650 align:middle line:84%
The thing in my case
is I'm going to be

00:20:13.650 --> 00:20:15.520 align:middle line:90%
able to relate to experience.

00:20:15.520 --> 00:20:17.500 align:middle line:84%
[INAUDIBLE] that you
